{"pagelen": 50, "values": [{"update": {"description": "This adds a section to the proposal that discusses scoping rules for referencing frames by name  in the world scope and model scope. It also explicitly allows every `//pose` to use `//pose[@relative_to]` in the appropriate scope, even if the objects are not sibling elements. I've updated the parsing stages and copied a bit of the example from pull request #16 and discussed the `//link/frame` idea as an alternative considered.\r\n\r\nI've targeted this at pull request #33 to avoid conflicts in the changes to the parsing stages.\r\n\r\nThis pull request is an alternative to pull request #16 and pull request #31.\r\n\r\nPreview: http://sdformat.org/tutorials?tut=pose_frame_semantics_proposal&branch=frame_scoping_rules", "title": "Proposal: scoping rules, allow everything to use //pose[@relative_to]", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "5e1e8d0d624d", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdf_tutorials/commit/5e1e8d0d624d.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdf_tutorials/commits/5e1e8d0d624d"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdf_tutorials.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdf_tutorials"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c7e79ad4-567f-412c-8738-289b2cd29c59}ts=markdown"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "sdf_tutorials", "full_name": "osrf/sdf_tutorials", "uuid": "{c7e79ad4-567f-412c-8738-289b2cd29c59}"}, "branch": {"name": "default"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "d90484c05af1", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdf_tutorials/commit/d90484c05af1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdf_tutorials/commits/d90484c05af1"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdf_tutorials.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdf_tutorials"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c7e79ad4-567f-412c-8738-289b2cd29c59}ts=markdown"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "sdf_tutor